com.inqwell.any

Class AnyTimerTask

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inqwell.any.AbstractComposite
      • com.inqwell.any.AbstractMap
        • com.inqwell.any.PropertyAccessMap
          • com.inqwell.any.AnyTimerTask
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Any, Composite, Map, Value, Serializable, Cloneable

    public class AnyTimerTask
extends PropertyAccessMap
implements Value, Cloneable
    Represents an expression to be run an at some time in the future. All the possibilities described in Timer are possible.

    When the timer matures a TIMER_TASK event is sent to the given input channel. This event is dispatched to execute the function contained within the timer task.

    • Constructor Detail

      • AnyTimerTask

        public AnyTimerTask(AnyFuncHolder.FuncHolder func,
                    DateI when,
                    LongI delay,
                    LongI period,
                    IntI delayOrRate,
                    BooleanI start,
                    Process p)
             throws AnyException
        Create and possibly schedule a timer task.
        Parameters:
        The - function to execute.
        p - The process to which the TIMER_TASK event will be written when the timer matures. Usually the process input channel.
        when - The absolute time when the function should be executed. If null then delay must be specified.
        delay - The relative delay before the function should be executed. Must be supplied if when is null, ignored otherwise.
        period - optional if the timer task is FIXED_DELAY, mandatory if the timer is FIXED_RATE. The repeat interval.
        delayOrRate - If AnyTimerTask.FIXED_DELAY then any period represents the interval between the last execution ending and the next one commencing. If AnyTimerTask.FIXED_RATE then period represents the interval between successive executions. Moot as the execution of the timer is just to send the TIMER_TASK event so the timer interval is decoupled from function execution.
        start - if true start the timer.
        Throws:
        AnyException

      • manualFire

        public void manualFire()
                throws AnyException
        Forces this timer to fire immediately regardless of whether it is scheduled to run at some time in the future. The lastRan property is set to the current system time.

        Any scheduling of this timer is not affected and it will fire again at nextRuns, if non-null.

        Throws:
        AnyException

      • setNull

        public void setNull()
        Puts this timer into a non-schedulable state. The implementation cancels any scheduling of this timer and sets the properties nextRuns and period to null and fixedOrDelay to FIXED_RATE.

        In general, the timer properties should all be considered undefined after calling this method.

        Specified by:
        setNull in interface Value
